title: Pre Conception Care
description:
Join Elle Brown, a beacon of wisdom in women's health and clinical nutrition, as she delves into the crucial topic of preconception care and postpartum nourishment. In this informative talk, Elle emphasises the importance of both partners' health in the journey to parenthood, highlighting key areas such as nutrient testing, prenatal supplementation, and environmental considerations.

She offers practical advice on assessing your health status, choosing quality prenatal vitamins, and reducing exposure to harmful chemicals in your daily life. Elle also stresses the significance of emotional preparation and partner communication during this transformative period. Whether you're planning to conceive soon or thinking about starting a family in the future, this talk provides valuable insights to optimise your health and set the stage for a smoother pregnancy and postpartum experience.
seo_meta_description: Expert Elle Brown discusses preconception care for couples, covering nutrient testing, supplements, and environmental factors. Essential for future parents.

title: Befriend Your Pelvic Floor Masterclass
description:
Join us for an eye-opening Masterclass that will change the way you think about your body's unsung hero - the pelvic floor. Led by Alex Farner and Emma Berry, this masterclass it's a refreshing, honest, and empowering exploration of a topic that's been shrouded in silence for far too long.

• Discover why your pelvic floor deserves your attention (hint: it's not just about babies!.)
• Learn how this invisible muscle group impacts everything from your emotions to your pleasure.
• Gain insights from two passionate professionals who approach pelvic health from unique angles
• Experience a guided breath practice with Alex to close the session.

Forget the embarrassment and misinformation. It's time to embrace and understand this crucial part of your body. Whether you're dealing with discomfort or curious about allowing and amplifying more pleasure in the pelvis, join Alex and Emma for a candid conversation that will leave you feeling informed, inspired, and in tune with your body.
seo_meta_description: Discover the power of your pelvic floor in this free masterclass with Alex Farner and Emma Berry. Learn how this crucial muscle group impacts your overall health, emotions, and pleasure. Join us for an empowering, honest discussion and guided practice.

title: Empowering The Mother Masterclass
description:
Pregnancy is one of the most monumental evolutions a woman can go through in her lifetime.
Join Alex, a teacher on The Fold who specializes in supporting women in pre and post natal health, with yoga. There will be a short guided practice, followed by education offered on common questions, modifications and advocacy on how to best support yourself physically, emotionally and mentally during practice (and life!).

This masterclass is for women at any stage of their pregnancy.

Through prenatal pregnancy and understanding the wisdom that the body holds, we can support the rapid growth and shifts a woman goes through physically and emotionally. She can be guided to step into her power from pregnancy to birth and beyond.
When a woman practices Yoga her baby has a direct experience of the change in her heart rate, the shift in her nervous system and the emotional quality is uniquely and absolutely felt and relayed to her little one.
This means, as much as we are supporting the Mother, we are also supporting the growth of healthy little nervous systems that know how to regulate, and what a privilege that is.
seo_title: Masterclass ~ Empowering The Mother - The Fold Online
seo_meta_description: Join Alex in "Empowering The Mother" masterclass, focusing on pre and post-natal yoga to support your well-being and your baby's health during pregnancy and beyond.

title: Navigating Menopause Masterclass
description:
An ever-increasing waistline. Brain fog and mood swings. Hot flushes and night sweats. Zero energy yet not able to stay asleep.
These are just a few of the symptoms that can occur during the (peri)-menopause. Symptoms can last several years and for many can be truly debilitating even if it is a natural process.
Whilst 100% of women born female will go through the menopause the good news is that there is a lot you can do in your lifestyle to help manage symptoms and reduce the risk of long-term metabolic diseases and support bone health. Whether one chooses to take HRT or not, lifestyle is formidable ally to the menopause journey.
This talk goes in depth into the most impactful approaches and science-based strategies that will support you and your clients to not only manage symptoms but ultimately thrive during the menopause transition.
seo_meta_description: Discover science-based strategies to manage (peri)menopause symptoms and thrive during this transition. Learn lifestyle approaches to alleviate common issues like weight gain, mood swings, and sleep problems while supporting long-term health.

title: Postnatal - Coming Back To The Mat
description:
When it comes to yoga with or around babies, anything goes!

Go easy on yourself coming back to the mat and consider anything you get done to be a win. Positioning your mini somewhere close to you can enable you to make eye contact, smile, wiggle your fingers as you move your arms, play peek a boo… or in today’s case Liam snoozed like a champ.

When baby’s having some floor time, get down with them and use some of these gentle stretching and conditioning exercises to provide relief from some of the stresses and physical symptoms of early parenting.

Zara is 9 weeks postpartum, Liam is her third baby born via cesarean.

title: Body Safety
description:
In this video we explore body safety for women.
This is a concept that I take every woman through, that I have the pleasure of working with.

The reason is that if our body doesn't feel safe, we don't ovulate.
Our body needs to feel safe to bleed, it needs to feel safe to fall pregnant, to orgasm, and to digest our food adequately.
It needs to feel safe to produce hormones so that our hormones function well.
It needs to feel safe so that we have low symptoms.
It needs to feel safe so that all our body systems and organ functions do what they're supposed to do.
seo_title: Body Safety - The Fold Online
seo_meta_description: Dive into the crucial concept of body safety for women's well-being on The Fold Online. Essential for ovulation, hormone function, digestion, and overall health.

title: Prenatal - Mirror Of The Neck & Cervix
description:
Cervix in latin translates to neck; the two are energetically and physically linked.
In this practice we release fascia around the neck, throat and jaw to access and soften our pelvic floor. Using humming, we release tension via the vagus nerve, allowing us to soften both areas of the body emotionally and physically.

I’ll guide you through some shapes and movement you might include in an active labor.

By practicing these tools throughout your pregnancy will help neural pathways form and strengthen, boosting communication between the body and brain.
seo_title: Prenatal - Mirror Of The Neck & Cervix for Women | Thefold Online
seo_meta_description: Dive into Prenatal - Mirror Of The Neck & Cervix for a holistic practice. Soften pelvic floor, release tension via humming, prep for active labor.
